    "title": "Me & My CPTS",
    "body": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24pt;\"><strong><img class=\"wp-image-2095 alignleft\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/1512170874431550696-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"259\" height=\"241\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/1512170874431550696-1.jpg 613w, /media-library/2016/07/1512170874431550696-1-300x279.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px\">My Personal CPTS Management Tool List.</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;My name is Shy Keenan and I have managed severe Civilian Post Traumatic Stress now for almost all&nbsp;of my life. I’m developing this page, so do pop back for updates. There will be links to products I use or recommend, that help me manage my Civilian Post Traumatic Stress&nbsp;or CPTS.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">They’ll also be some links to other peoples products I’d like to see into&nbsp;developed ‘CPTS bespoke’ versions of …</p>\n<p><strong>Before we get started, must make a few things clear ..and there are some rules.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1/</strong> CPTS CAN KILL! No one patient is the same, there is no ‘one glove fits all’. It is, in my opinion, first and foremost ‘a medical condition’ that can, if not properly treated, trigger and exacerbate life-threatening medical and mental health conditions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2/</strong> I’m a patient NOT a Doctor ..who is the only person who should be diagnosing/establishing/managing/changing your CPTS treatment, ever.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3/</strong> I manage my CPTS medical condition with the support of my NHS medical professional care team.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">a/ I develop my own (drug-free) CPTS management tools.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">b/ I work with product makers to develop CPTS friendly versions of their products, to what are in fact ..millions of CPTS managers …</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">c/ I work to help educate the NHS on what really helps our Civilian CPTS kind.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4/</strong> Free is always warmly welcome, however, there can be no sponsor on this page. This page is only for what I know works specifically for me and my CPTS.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">That said, whilst we are all very different, we do have some things in common and I want to use this page to share (with others like me) information about ‘what really helps’ me to manage my CPTS.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">….</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Below are some pics &amp; links for products I wish could be prescribed instead of drugs and other products that have turned out to be must have&nbsp;CPTS management tools&nbsp;…</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.shapemaster.co.uk/index.php/exercise-equipment/multimaster\">Shapemaster’s daily ‘Power Assisted Exercise’ </a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"http://foscam.uk.com/\">Foscam&nbsp;allows&nbsp;you&nbsp;to&nbsp;</a>see and speak to whoever is at your door before you open it. </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Would love to see these Orrbs in every public building&nbsp;</span>and NHS p<span style=\"color: #333333;\">rescribed&nbsp;these to our CPTS kind.</span><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></em></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/GmWuamJI7BQ\" width=\"620\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">My PTSD needs sunshine, even when the sun doesn’t shine.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.sad.co.uk/en-UK/\"><img class=\"wp-image-1597 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/sad-banner.jpg\" alt=\"sad banner\" width=\"247\" height=\"80\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/sad-banner.jpg 1185w, /media-library/2016/07/sad-banner-300x97.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/sad-banner-768x248.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/sad-banner-1024x331.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/sad-banner-700x226.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 247px) 100vw, 247px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Kitchen Garden – I use&nbsp;‘Weapons Of Mass Distraction’&nbsp;to help me manage my PTSD.</span><a href=\"http://www.growfruitandveg.co.uk/\"><img class=\"wp-image-1600 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden.jpg\" alt=\"ptsdgarden\" width=\"282\" height=\"79\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden.jpg 1135w, /media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden-300x84.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden-768x215.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden-1024x287.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/ptsdgarden-700x196.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 282px) 100vw, 282px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">I use&nbsp;many ‘Weapons Of Mass Distraction’&nbsp;to help me manage my PTSD, like art.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.ido3dart.com/\">&nbsp;</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">About my PTSD Mobility.</span><a href=\"https://www.revolverobotics.com/video-conferencing-robot/\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1607\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/kubi2.jpg\" alt=\"kubi2\" width=\"666\" height=\"269\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/kubi2.jpg 1324w, /media-library/2016/07/kubi2-300x121.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/kubi2-768x310.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/kubi2-1024x414.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/kubi2-700x283.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"><br>\n</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">My PTSD likes to know who is on the phone before I answer it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://home.bt.com/news/bt-life/how-to-control-nuisance-and-unwanted-calls-11363906182494\"><img class=\"wp-image-1611 alignnone\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/BT8500Quad_large.jpg\" alt=\"BT8500Quad_large\" width=\"585\" height=\"285\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/BT8500Quad_large.jpg 480w, /media-library/2016/07/BT8500Quad_large-300x146.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">An Aroma Diffuser helps me manage what my PTSD can smell.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.stressnomore.co.uk/\"><img class=\"wp-image-1618 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/diff.jpg\" alt=\"diff\" width=\"592\" height=\"202\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/diff.jpg 1049w, /media-library/2016/07/diff-300x102.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/diff-768x262.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/diff-1024x349.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/diff-700x239.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 592px) 100vw, 592px\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">When</span></a><span style=\"color: #333333;\"> my PTSD needs me to&nbsp;control my body&nbsp;temperature fast.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.dyson.co.uk/\"><img class=\"wp-image-1620 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/dyson.jpg\" alt=\"dyson\" width=\"621\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/dyson.jpg 1179w, /media-library/2016/07/dyson-300x88.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/dyson-768x225.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/dyson-1024x301.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/dyson-700x205.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Music&nbsp;– More&nbsp;brilliant ‘Weapons Of Mass Distraction’&nbsp;to help me manage my PTSD.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.music-maker.com/us/music-maker-jam/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1650\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA.jpg\" alt=\"QujqwuKA\" width=\"620\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA.jpg 2560w, /media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA-300x188.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA-768x480.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA-1024x640.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/QujqwuKA-700x438.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.music-maker.com/us/music-maker-jam/\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">My</span></a><span style=\"color: #333333;\"> PTSD fully supports Civilian PTSD Service Dogs.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.thephoenixpost.com/ptsd-garden/\"><img class=\"wp-image-1624 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs.jpg\" alt=\"CPTSD dogs\" width=\"588\" height=\"187\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs.jpg 1334w, /media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs-300x96.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs-768x245.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs-1024x326.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/CPTSD-dogs-700x223.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 588px) 100vw, 588px\"></a><span style=\"color: #333333;\">For when my PTSD needs me to manage what I see &amp; hear.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.thephoenixpost.com/ptsd-garden/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1630\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/see.jpg\" alt=\"see\" width=\"622\" height=\"175\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/see.jpg 1263w, /media-library/2016/07/see-300x85.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/see-768x216.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/see-1024x289.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2016/07/see-700x197.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 622px) 100vw, 622px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The future of managing&nbsp;what my PTSD can see&nbsp;&amp; hear.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-hololens/en-us\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1740\" src=\"/media-library/2016/07/glases.jpg\" alt=\"Hololens\" width=\"614\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"/media-library/2016/07/glases.jpg 897w, /media-library/2016/07/glases-300x174.jpg 300w, /media-library/2016/07/glases-768x445.jpg 768w, /media-library/2016/07/glases-700x406.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\"></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">My hyper sensitive PTSD skin doesn’t like ‘on skin’ products or mossy bites, so I use the products from <a href=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/s/ref=as_li_ss_tl?merchant=A3RNTQNUTA98CC&amp;fallThrough=1&amp;linkCode=sl2&amp;tag=wwwkardycouk-21&amp;linkId=01299eb2d75125ed3cf487e5332fa601\">the Linked Supply team</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/s/ref=as_li_ss_tl?merchant=A3RNTQNUTA98CC&amp;fallThrough=1&amp;linkCode=sl2&amp;tag=wwwkardycouk-21&amp;linkId=01299eb2d75125ed3cf487e5332fa601\"><img class=\"wp-image-1866 aligncenter\" src=\"/media-library/2017/06/BB.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"/media-library/2017/06/BB.jpg 1194w, /media-library/2017/06/BB-300x156.jpg 300w, /media-library/2017/06/BB-768x399.jpg 768w, /media-library/2017/06/BB-1024x532.jpg 1024w, /media-library/2017/06/BB-700x363.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\"></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"addtoany_share_save_container addtoany_content addtoany_content_bottom\"><div class=\"a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_16 addtoany_list\" data-a2a-url=\"/?p=1571\" data-a2a-title=\"Me &amp; My CPTS\"><a class=\"a2a_button_facebook\" href=\"https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=%2F%2F%3Fp%3D1571&amp;linkname=Me%20%26%20My%20CPTS\" title=\"Facebook\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a class=\"a2a_button_twitter\" href=\"https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=%2F%2F%3Fp%3D1571&amp;linkname=Me%20%26%20My%20CPTS\" title=\"Twitter\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a class=\"a2a_dd a2a_counter addtoany_share_save addtoany_share\" href=\"https://www.addtoany.com/share\"><img src=\"https://static.addtoany.com/buttons/share_save_171_16.png\" alt=\"Share\"></a></div></div>",
